Cell.Text: [S] I'm guessing you're the newcomer then?

Node.Caption: C00EorlundIntroTopic: Vilkas sent me with his sword.

Cell.Text: Oh, don't worry too much about it. They were all whelps once. They just might not like to talk about it. | And don't always just do what you're told. Nobody rules anybody in the Companions.

Node.Caption: C00ImAScrub: Does Vilkas always send newcomers on errands?

Cell.Text: Not actually a Companion myself, but none of them know how to work a forge properly, and I'm honored to serve them. | My name is Eorlund Gray-Mane. I work the Skyforge. Best steel in all of Skyrim. All of Tamriel.
That attitude would get you far, if you were some stuffy merchant or a Jarl's footstool. | Around here, you'll want to learn to live your own life. Remember, nobody rules anybody in the Companions.

Node.Caption: C00EorlundImAGoodBoy: I'm just doing what I'm asked.

Cell.Text: Well, I'm not sure how they've managed it, but they have. No leaders since Ysgramor. | Kodlak is the Harbinger, and he's a sort of advisor for the whole group, but every man is his own. Every woman, her own.

Node.Caption: C00CompanionsHierarchy: Someone has to be in charge, though.

Cell.Text: I have a favor to ask.
[S] G|This isn't a command. Just decency. Help out an old blacksmith. I've got to get back to my work.

Node.Caption: C00EorlundWaitASec: Didn't you just tell me not to be a servant?
C00EorlundHappyToHelp: I'm happy to lend a hand.

Cell.Text: I've been working on a shield for Aela. | My wife is in mourning and I need to get back to her soon. I'd be much obliged if you could take this to Aela for me.
Yes, lad, you've been raised into the Companions, I hear. | I can fashion whatever kind of weapon you want. Finest forge in Skyrim, right here before you.

Node.Caption: C00EorlundBranchTopic: I was told you would have a weapon for me.

Cell.Text: [S] G|A blade! It will be as sharp as Fralia's tongue!
[S] G|Ah, the sneaky type, eh? I think we can fix you right up.
[S] G|Sure you can handle that? Ha! Of course you can.
[S] G|Now that's a smart weapon. Light, strong, useful. Crack some skulls for me.

[S] You know, since Kodlak's funeral the Skyforge feels more... awake. | It's always been said that the souls of the heroes of old are what give Skyforge steel its strength. | But I think the forge knows the greatness of Kodlak's soul. I can't really explain, but it feels like it's... young. | I'll wager it could now forge metal the likes of which hasn't been seen since eras long forgotten. | I'm eager to try.
